  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth\nVersion: 1.5.0-unstable-2d7d7ef2\nProtocol Versions: [63 62 61]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.6.2\nOS: darwin\nGOPATH=\nGOROOT=/usr/local/Cellar/go/1.6.2/libexec\n\nOS & Version: OSX\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\n#### Expected behaviour\n\ngeth init is safe enough to prevent  corrupting the main blockchain.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nThere are 2 issues:\n- if --datadir is not provided, it defaults to the mainnet\n- if --datadir is provided _after_ the init command, it defaults to mainnet\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nAll of the following will damage your mainnet blockchain, beware! While this is understandable for the first command, for the 2 others, you probably donÂ´t expect your mainnet to get touched.\n- geth init genesis.json\n- geth -datadir /Users/chevdor/Library/Ethereum/privatenet/ init genesis.json (notice the error, -datadir instead of --datadir)\n- geth init genesis.json --datadir /Users/chevdor/Library/Ethereum/privatenet/\n",
