    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "For the record, you don't overwrite any chain data. When you made a mistake or forgot the `--datadir` the only thing that happens is that you tell geth \"block 0 (i.e. genesis) = [this block]\". You can do this as many times as you want and hence it allows you to revert back to any previous genesis block. \n",
